    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe inlay hint decoration provider in `runtime/lua/vim/lsp/inlay_hint.lua` crashes with `Invalid 'col': out of range` when a cached hint position references a column beyond the current line length (e.g. after an edit shortens a line).\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Open a file with an LSP that provides inlay hints (e.g. tsgo, typescript-language-server)\n2. Have inlay hints enabled\n3. Edit a line to make it shorter than a hint's character position (e.g. delete text at end of line)\n4. The next redraw triggers the error\n\n### Error\n\n```\nDecoration provider \"win\" (ns=nvim.lsp.inlayhint):\nLua: ...runtime/lua/vim/lsp/inlay_hint.lua:362: Invalid 'col': out of range\nstack traceback:\n  [C]: in function 'nvim_buf_set_extmark'\n  ...runtime/lua/vim/lsp/inlay_hint.lua:362: in function <...runtime/lua/vim/lsp/inlay_hint.lua:316>\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe decoration provider should bounds-check the column before calling `nvim_buf_set_extmark`, either clamping or skipping hints with out-of-range positions.\n\n### My solution\n\nI solved it with this, but I don't know if that's the best approach here -- \n\n```lua\n-- Before:\nfor pos, vt in pairs(hint_virtual_texts) do\n  api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(bufnr, namespace, lnum, pos, {\n    virt_text_pos = 'inline',\n    ephemeral = false,\n    virt_text = vt,\n  })\nend\n\n-- After:\nfor pos, vt in pairs(hint_virtual_texts) do\n  local line_len = #(api.nvim_buf_get_lines(bufnr, lnum, lnum + 1, false)[1] or '')\n  if pos <= line_len then\n    api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(bufnr, namespace, lnum, pos, {\n      virt_text_pos = 'inline',\n      ephemeral = false,\n      virt_text = vt,\n    })\n  end\nend\n```\n\n### Neovim version\n\nNVIM v0.12.2",
